{
  "texts": [
    "AI-enabled UAV-ISACThe terrestrial ISAC network may face the challenges of limited service range due to the blocked lineof-sight (LoS) links from the ISAC-BS to the distant users or targets.",
    "Compared with the terrestrial BS, the UAV can establish the LoS links more flexibly and quickly due to its high mobility [266].",
    "This characteristic not only improves the communication QoS, but also benefits the target acquisition, because the radar acquisition prefers the LoS links.",
    "Consequently, there is a trend to integrate the UAV into ISAC networks for performance enhancement [80].",
    "However, it can be challenging to jointly design the signal processing, resource allocation, as well as the trajectory of the UAV within UAV-ISAC networks, especially when the environment is dynamic and the dimension of the optimization variables is large."
  ]
}